    64→
    65→/* 3. Blocks - only when needed */
    66→.card {
    67→  background: var(--color-surface-secondary);
    68→  border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    69→  padding: var(--space-lg);
    70→  box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
    71→}
    72→
    73→/* 4. Exception - data attributes for state */
    74→[data-state="error"] { color: var(--color-error); }
    75→[data-layout="compact"] { gap: var(--space-s); }
    76→```
    77→
    78→**Recommendation for Socialaize:**
    79→- Migrate away from strict BEM naming (`block__element--modifier`)
    80→- Use composition utilities for layout (grid, stack, switcher, cluster)
    81→- Reserve component class names for complex interactive elements only
    82→- Use data attributes for state variations (loading, disabled, active)
    83→
    84→### Cascade Layers (@layer)
    85→
    86→```css
    87→/* Define layer order once */
    88→@layer reset, theme, composition, utilities, components, overrides;
    89→
    90→@layer reset {
    91→  * { margin: 0; padding: 0; }
    92→}
    93→
    94→@layer theme {
    95→  :root {
    96→    --color-primary: oklch(50% 0.2 240);
    97→    --space-unit: 0.25rem;
    98→  }
    99→}
   100→
   101→@layer composition {
   102→  .stack { /* ... */ }
   103→  .switcher { /* ... */ }
   104→}
   105→
   106→@layer utilities {
   107→  .p-4 { padding: calc(var(--space-unit) * 4); }
   108→}
   109→
   110→@layer components {
   111→  .button { /* component styles */ }
   112→}
   113→
   114→@layer overrides {
   115→  /* Emergency fixes - lowest cascade priority */
   116→}
   117→```
   118→
   119→**Benefits:**
   120→- Architecture without rigidity
   121→- Explicit precedence regardless of order
   122→- Can inject new styles without specificity wars
