   126→## 2. Color & Theming Systems
   127→
   128→### OKLCH/OKLAB Adoption (93% Browser Support)
   129→
   130→**Why OKLCH > HSL/RGB:**
   131→
   132→| Aspect | HSL | RGB | OKLCH |
   133→|--------|-----|-----|-------|
   134→| Dark Mode | ❌ Washed out | ❌ Requires manual tweaking | ✅ Maintains saturation |
   135→| Contrast | Manual WCAG calcs | Manual WCAG calcs | ✅ Perceived luminance |
   136→| Color Spaces | Limited | Limited | ✅ P3 (30% wider gamut) |
   137→| Perceptual Uniformity | Poor | Poor | ✅ Excellent |
   138→
   139→```css
   140→/* OKLCH Color System */
   141→:root {
   142→  /* Primary Brand: Teal */
   143→  --color-primary-50: oklch(95% 0.05 240);
   144→  --color-primary-100: oklch(90% 0.08 240);
   145→  --color-primary-200: oklch(80% 0.12 240);
   146→  --color-primary-300: oklch(70% 0.15 240);
   147→  --color-primary-400: oklch(60% 0.18 240);
   148→  --color-primary-500: oklch(50% 0.2 240);  /* Base color */
   149→  --color-primary-600: oklch(45% 0.18 240);
   150→  --color-primary-700: oklch(40% 0.15 240);
   151→  --color-primary-800: oklch(30% 0.12 240);
   152→  --color-primary-900: oklch(20% 0.08 240);
   153→
   154→  /* Semantic Colors - consistent across light/dark */
   155→  --color-success-500: oklch(60% 0.15 140);  /* Green */
   156→  --color-warning-500: oklch(65% 0.18 70);   /* Amber */
   157→  --color-error-500: oklch(55% 0.2 20);      /* Red */
   158→  --color-info-500: oklch(60% 0.16 240);     /* Blue */
   159→
   160→  /* Surface Colors - semantic naming */
   161→  --color-surface-primary: oklch(98% 0 0);     /* Light backgrounds */
   162→  --color-surface-secondary: oklch(95% 0 0);   /* Cards, panels */
   163→  --color-surface-tertiary: oklch(92% 0 0);    /* Nested elements */
   164→  --color-surface-inverse: oklch(8% 0 0);      /* Dark inverse */
   165→
   166→  /* Text - perceptually consistent */
   167→  --color-text-primary: oklch(15% 0.02 240);
   168→  --color-text-secondary: oklch(45% 0.02 240);
   169→  --color-text-tertiary: oklch(65% 0.02 240);
   170→  --color-text-placeholder: oklch(75% 0.01 240);
   171→}
   172→
   173→/* Dark mode - automatic with same tokens */
   174→@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
   175→  :root {
   176→    --color-surface-primary: oklch(15% 0 0);
   177→    --color-surface-secondary: oklch(20% 0 0);
   178→    --color-surface-tertiary: oklch(25% 0 0);
   179→    --color-text-primary: oklch(95% 0.02 240);
   180→    --color-text-secondary: oklch(75% 0.02 240);
   181→    --color-text-tertiary: oklch(55% 0.02 240);
   182→  }
   183→}
   184→```
   185→
   186→**Key OKLCH Values:**
   187→- **L (Lightness):** 0-100% - perceived brightness (better than HSL's lightness)
   188→- **C (Chroma):** 0-0.4 typical - color intensity (wider than HSL saturation)
   189→- **H (Hue):** 0-360° - color wheel
   190→
   191→**Dark Mode Luminance Rule:**
   192→```javascript
   193→// OKLCH detection: if L > 0.6, it's a light color
   194→const isDarkMode = lightness < 0.6;
   195→// This works automatically without special dark mode palettes
   196→```
   197→
   198→### Semantic Token Naming (CTI Pattern)
   199→
   200→```
   201→Category > Type > Item > State
   202→color > background > input > disabled
   203→```
   204→
   205→```css
   206→/* Good semantic naming */
   207→--color-surface-primary-default
   208→--color-surface-primary-hover
   209→--color-surface-primary-active
   210→--color-surface-primary-disabled
   211→
   212→--color-border-input-default
   213→--color-border-input-focus
   214→--color-border-input-error
   215→
   216→--color-text-action-default
   217→--color-text-action-hover
   218→--color-text-action-disabled
   219→
   220→/* Avoid */
   221→--color-blue-500        /* Not semantic */
   222→--color-button          /* Too vague */
   223→--primary-color         /* Not hierarchical */
   224→```
