   228→## 3. Typography & Spacing
   229→
   230→### Fluid Typography with clamp()
   231→
   232→**Replace breakpoint-based sizing with continuous scaling:**
   233→
   234→```css
   235→/* Fluid typography pattern */
   236→:root {
   237→  /* Base font sizes - scale smoothly across viewport */
   238→  --font-size-xs: clamp(0.75rem, 0.7rem + 0.25vw, 0.875rem);
   239→  --font-size-sm: clamp(0.875rem, 0.8rem + 0.37vw, 1rem);
   240→  --font-size-base: clamp(1rem, 0.9rem + 0.5vw, 1.125rem);
   241→  --font-size-lg: clamp(1.125rem, 1rem + 0.62vw, 1.25rem);
   242→  --font-size-xl: clamp(1.25rem, 1.1rem + 0.75vw, 1.5rem);
   243→  --font-size-2xl: clamp(1.5rem, 1.3rem + 1vw, 2rem);
   244→  --font-size-3xl: clamp(1.875rem, 1.6rem + 1.25vw, 2.5rem);
   245→  --font-size-4xl: clamp(2.25rem, 1.9rem + 1.75vw, 3rem);
   246→  --font-size-5xl: clamp(3rem, 2.5rem + 2.5vw, 4rem);
   247→
   248→  /* Formula: clamp(min, preferred, max)
   249→     min: smallest acceptable size
   250→     preferred: scales with vw (usually min + 1-2vw)
   251→     max: largest acceptable size
   252→  */
   253→}
   254→
   255→/* Display heading sizes */
   256→h1 { font-size: var(--font-size-4xl); }
   257→h2 { font-size: var(--font-size-3xl); }
   258→h3 { font-size: var(--font-size-2xl); }
   259→p { font-size: var(--font-size-base); }
   260→small { font-size: var(--font-size-sm); }
   261→```
   262→
   263→**Container-Relative Fluid Typography (2025 Evolution):**
   264→
   265→```css
   266→@container (min-width: 400px) {
   267→  .heading {
   268→    /* Typography scales with container, not viewport */
   269→    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 1rem + 5cqi, 2.5rem);
   270→  }
   271→}
   272→
   273→/* cqi = container query inline (width-based) */
   274→/* cqb = container query block (height-based) */
   275→```
   276→
   277→### Modular Type Scale
   278→
   279→```css
   280→:root {
   281→  /* Base size + ratios */
   282→  --font-size-base: 1rem;
   283→  --type-scale-ratio: 1.125; /* Minor second interval */
   284→
   285→  --font-size-xs: calc(var(--font-size-base) / (var(--type-scale-ratio) * 4));
   286→  --font-size-sm: calc(var(--font-size-base) / (var(--type-scale-ratio) * 2));
   287→  --font-size-lg: calc(var(--font-size-base) * var(--type-scale-ratio));
   288→  --font-size-xl: calc(var(--font-size-base) * (var(--type-scale-ratio) * 2));
   289→  --font-size-2xl: calc(var(--font-size-base) * (var(--type-scale-ratio) * 3));
   290→}
   291→
   292→/* Common ratios:
   293→   1.067 = Minor second (minimal)
   294→   1.125 = Major second (small steps)
   295→   1.2 = Minor third (moderate)
   296→   1.333 = Major third (strong)
   297→   1.618 = Golden ratio (elegant)
   298→*/
   299→```
   300→
   301→### Fluid Spacing System
   302→
   303→```css
   304→:root {
   305→  /* Base unit - all spacing derives from this */
   306→  --space-unit: 0.25rem; /* 4px base */
   307→
   308→  /* T-shirt sizing via clamp() */
   309→  --space-xs: clamp(0.25rem, 0.2rem + 0.25vw, 0.5rem);
   310→  --space-sm: clamp(0.5rem, 0.4rem + 0.25vw, 0.75rem);
   311→  --space-md: clamp(0.75rem, 0.65rem + 0.5vw, 1rem);
   312→  --space-lg: clamp(1rem, 0.85rem + 0.75vw, 1.5rem);
   313→  --space-xl: clamp(1.5rem, 1.2rem + 1vw, 2rem);
   314→  --space-2xl: clamp(2rem, 1.6rem + 1.5vw, 3rem);
   315→  --space-3xl: clamp(3rem, 2.3rem + 2vw, 4rem);
   316→
   317→  /* Also support multiples for composition */
   318→  --gap-sm: var(--space-sm);
   319→  --gap-md: var(--space-md);
   320→  --gap-lg: var(--space-lg);
   321→}
   322→
   323→/* Usage */
   324→.stack { gap: var(--gap-md); }
   325→.card { padding: var(--space-lg); }
   326→.section { margin-block: var(--space-2xl); }
   327→```
